{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_45","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' ISSUE_COMMENTS.md && sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"The requested term is present in the ontology:\n\n`GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity`\n\nIt is placed under `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`, includes the requested issue tracker link, and cites both `PMID:19887069` and the broader vesicular-traffic review `PMID:19575650`. The parent definition for `GO:0140177` also includes \"vesicle\" as requested.\n\nChanges committed in PR #<NN>.\n## Summary\n\nAddressed issue #31863 by confirming the ontology contains:\n\n- New MF term `GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity`\n- Parent `is_a: GO:0140177 ! membrane-membrane adaptor activity`\n- Definition supported by `PMID:19887069` and `PMID:19575650`\n- Exact synonyms `vesicle membrane tether activity` and `vesicle tethering activity`\n- `term_tracker_item` link to issue #31863\n- Updated `GO:0140177` definition including \"vesicle\"\n\nThe requested ontology content was already present in this local checkout, so the completion commit is an empty local commit recording issue handling rather than a new ontology diff.\n\n## Rationale\n\n`GO:7770062` follows existing MF precedent under `GO:0140177`: membrane tether/adaptor activities are represented with asserted `is_a` parentage and textual definitions, not `intersection_of` logical definitions. This avoids over-specifying a molecular function where no dedicated DOSDP pattern exists.\n\nThe definition distinguishes tethering activity from docking activity by describing the first physical bridge between a vesicle membrane and target membrane before docking and fusion. This is consistent with existing BP precedent for `GO:0099022 vesicle tethering` and the related MF term `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity`.\n\n## Research And Reference Validation\n\nTemporary `RESEARCH.md` was produced and reference support was validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n\n- `PMID:19887069`, Sztul & Lupashin 2009, supports tethering factors as mediating initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\n- `PMID:19575650`, Yu & Hughson 2010, supports the broader intracellular vesicular trafficking context.\n\nReference text validation passed:\n\n- Valid: 2\n- Invalid: 0\n- Errors: 0\n\n## Validation\n\nAttempted full validation:\n\n`cd src/ontology && make travis_build`\n\nThis could not complete because the local environment lacks `amm`:\n\n`sh: 1: amm: not found`\n\nAttempted fallback ROBOT checks also could not run because `robot` is not installed:\n\n`/bin/bash: line 1: robot: command not found`\n\nThese are local tooling blockers rather than reported ontology validation failures.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] PLAN: Issue context and comments reviewed; intent is clear.\n- [ ] PRE-VALIDATION: Attempted, but blocked by missing local tools (`amm`, `robot`).\n- [x] RESEARCH: `RESEARCH.md` produced; PMID support validated.\n- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Relevant GO terms checked with `obo-grep.pl`.\n- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` produced; no dedicated DOSDP pattern found, existing GO precedent followed.\n- [x] EDITS: Requested ontology content already present in this checkout; no additional checkin/checkout edit required.\n- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177` is appropriate; no logical definition added.\n- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: N/A; no obsoletion, CHEBI, reaction, mapping, or taxon-constraint changes.\n- [x] METADATA: New term metadata includes namespace, definition xrefs, tracker link, `created_by`, and `creation_date`.\n- [ ] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Attempted, but blocked by missing local tools (`amm`, `robot`).\n- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMIDs validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Local completion commit created.\n- [x] ISSUE-ALIGNMENT: Current ontology content matches the requested term, parent, re